<procedure xmlns:dc="http://www.purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" xmlns:rdf="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="http://www.s1000d.org/S1000D_6/xml_schema_flat/proced.xsd">
  <title>Bicycle Pre-Ride Check - Crew Procedure</title>
  <introduction>
    <para>This document outlines the crew procedure for a pre-ride bicycle check, ensuring rider safety and optimal performance. It details the steps for inspecting critical components and performing necessary adjustments.</para>
  </introduction>
  <step>
    <title>Crew Procedure Steps</title>
    <step_item>
      <title>1. Brakes</title>
      <item>
        <bullet>Inspect brake pads for wear.</bullet>
        <bullet>Ensure brake levers operate smoothly.</bullet>
        <bullet>Verify cable integrity (no cuts or fraying).</bullet>
        <bullet>Confirm proper brake function - both front and rear.</bullet>
      </item>
    </step_item>
    <step_item>
      <title>2. Tires</title>
      <item>
        <bullet>Tire pressure (see table below for recommended ranges).</bullet>
        <bullet>Inspect tires for cracks, splits, or embedded objects.</bullet>
      </item>
      <table_data>
        <header_row>
          <header>Header</header>
          <header>Terrain</header>
          <header>Minimum Pressure</header>
          <header>Maximum Pressure</header>
        </header_row>
        <data_row>
          <row>Row</row>
          <terrain>Off Road</terrain>
          <min_pressure>35 lbs</min_pressure>
          <max_pressure>40 lbs</max_pressure>
        </data_row>
        <data_row>
          <row>Row</row>
          <terrain>On Road</terrain>
          <min_pressure>55 lbs</min_pressure>
          <max_pressure>60 lbs</max_pressure>
        </data_row>
      </table_data>
    </step_item>
    <step_item>
      <title>3. Wheels</title>
      <item>
        <bullet>Spin wheels to verify smooth rotation.</bullet>
        <bullet>Listen for unusual noises indicating bearing issues.</bullet>
        <bullet>Inspect spokes for breakage.</bullet>
        <bullet>Ensure spokes are tight.</bullet>
        <bullet>Confirm axle nuts are securely tightened.</bullet>
        <bullet>Confirm wheel is 'true' (not wobbling).</bullet>
      </item>
    </step_item>
    <step_item>
      <title>4. Headset</title>
      <item>
        <bullet>Ensure headset bearings are tight and smooth.</bullet>
      </item>
    </step_item>
    <step_item>
      <title>5. Chain</title>
      <item>
        <bullet>Verify easy movement of chain links.</bullet>
      </item>
    </step_item>
    <step_item>
      <title>6. Handlebar &amp; Stem</title>
      <para>Do *not* ride with a cracked stem.</para>
      <condition_action>
        <condition>Stem Cracked</condition>
        <action>Replace stem immediately.</action>
      </condition_action>
      <condition_action>
        <condition>Stem Loose</condition>
        <action>Tighten stem.</action>
      </condition_action>
      <condition_action>
        <condition>Handlebars Twist</condition>
        <action>Tighten clamp bolt.</action>
      </condition_action>
    </step_item>
    <step_item>
      <title>7. Computer Display</title>
      <para>Ensure the computer is displaying accurate information (example):</para>
      <table_data>
        <header_row>
          <header>Header</header>
          <header>Component</header>
          <header>Displayed Value</header>
        </header_row>
        <data_row>
          <row>Row</row>
          <component>Speed</component>
          <displayed_value>0 mph</displayed_value>
        </data_row>
        <data_row>
          <row>Row</row>
          <component>Distance</component>
          <displayed_value>0 miles</displayed_value>
        </data_row>
      </table_data>
    </step_item>
  </step>
  <notes>
    <para>This procedure is a guideline; adapt it based on specific bicycle types and rider needs.</para>
    <para>Regular maintenance and inspection are crucial for safety and performance.</para>
    <para>Always prioritize safety; if unsure about any component, seek professional assistance.</para>
  </notes>
</procedure>